    "Content loss: Content loss 1, 25, 26 is introduced into the SISR task to evaluate the perceptual quality of images.",
    "Specifically, we employ a pre-trained classification network to measure the semantic differences between images.",
    "This network is denoted as φ, and the high-level representations extracted at layer l-th are represented as φ (l) (I).",
    "The content loss is defined as the Euclidean distance between the high-level representations of the two images, as shown below:",
    "Where h l, w l, and c l represent the height, width, and number of channels of the representations on layer l, respectively."
